    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-15T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-15T08:35:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20 Mission/7–1544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-15T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >July 15, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 15—12:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>505. Department’s 407 dated July 4. After consulting with General Ridley who
                    requested that matter be held up one week until his progress report (based on
                    report to Washington dated May 31<note n="21" xml:id="d438fn21">Not printed; see
                        letter of June 23 from the Secretary of War, <ref target="#pg_412">p.
                            412</ref>.</note>) had been presented to and read by Iranian Government,
                    I have now handed an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to Prime Minister
                    setting forth War Department’s <pb facs="0433" n="421" xml:id="pg_421"/> wishes
                    respecting withdrawal Ridley Mission as of November 1, 1944. Saed promised to
                    take up question with Council of Ministers and let me know immediately his
                    Government’s wishes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
